  Statement of Purpose

   The California Integrated Waste Management Board (CIWMB) maintains this
   Web site to enhance public access to information and services provided
   by the Board.

   The CIWMB's goals for the Web site include:
     * Provide timely and convenient access to Board publications and
       information about all of the Board's programs.
     * Reduce waste generation and increase the productivity and
       effectiveness of Board staff through electronic dissemination of
       Board documents and other information.
     * Through the use of external links, provide the Board's Web site
       users with convenient access to other resources available on the
       Internet.
     * Make effective use of current and evolving Internet technologies to
       maximize benefits to the Board's clients and help California
       achieve 50 percent diversion of its waste from landfills.
     * Provide an archive of past program activities for the use of the
       public and CIWMB staff.

  Accessibility

   Web Access Symbol (for people with disabilities) This site includes
   accessibility features to accommodate the needs of disabled users. If
   you need information about these features or have suggestions, please
   contact the Public Affairs Office at (916) 341-6300.

   Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) Statement
   The California Integrated Waste Management Board (CIWMB) does not
   discriminate on the basis of disability in access to its programs.
   Persons with hearing impairments can reach the CIWMB through the
   California Relay Service, 1-800-735-2929.

  Whom to Contact

   Questions about the content of a specific portion of the CIWMB Web site
   should be referred to the contact listed in the footer of that page.

   Questions about the general content of the CIWMB Web site should be
   directed to the Public Affairs Office at (916) 341-6300.

   Questions about the technical aspects of the site should be e-mailed to
   the CIWMB Webmaster.

